<refsect1>
<title>Details</title>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="PclBool-struct"/>PclBool</title>
<indexterm><primary>PclBool</primary></indexterm><programlisting>typedef struct _PclBool PclBool;</programlisting>
<para>

</para></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="PCL-TRUE:CAPS"/>PCL_TRUE</title>
<indexterm><primary>PCL_TRUE</primary></indexterm><programlisting>#define PCL_TRUE (pcl_bool_get_instance_true ())
</programlisting>
<para>

</para></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="PCL-FALSE:CAPS"/>PCL_FALSE</title>
<indexterm><primary>PCL_FALSE</primary></indexterm><programlisting>#define PCL_FALSE (pcl_bool_get_instance_false ())
</programlisting>
<para>

</para></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="pcl-bool-get-type-object"/>pcl_bool_get_type_object ()</title>
<indexterm><primary>pcl_bool_get_type_object</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="PclObject">PclObject</link>*  pcl_bool_get_type_object        (void);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns the type object for <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link>.  During runtime this is the built-in
object <literal>bool</literal>.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> a borrowed reference to the type object for <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="pcl-bool-get-instance-true"/>pcl_bool_get_instance_true ()</title>
<indexterm><primary>pcl_bool_get_instance_true</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="PclObject">PclObject</link>*  pcl_bool_get_instance_true      (void);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns the singleton instance of <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link> representing true.  During
runtime this is the built-in object <literal>True</literal>.
</para>
<para>
Do not call this function directly.  Instead, use <link linkend="PCL-TRUE:CAPS"><type>PCL_TRUE</type></link>.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> a borrowed reference to the singleton instance of <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link>
         representing true
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="pcl-bool-get-instance-false"/>pcl_bool_get_instance_false ()</title>
<indexterm><primary>pcl_bool_get_instance_false</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="PclObject">PclObject</link>*  pcl_bool_get_instance_false     (void);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns the singleton instance of <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link> representing false.  During
runtime this is the built-in object <literal>False</literal>.
</para>
<para>
Do not call this function directly.  Instead, use <link linkend="PCL-FALSE:CAPS"><type>PCL_FALSE</type></link>.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> a borrowed reference to the singleton instance of <link linkend="PclBool"><type>PclBool</type></link>
         representing false
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="pcl-bool-from-boolean"/>pcl_bool_from_boolean ()</title>
<indexterm><primary>pcl_bool_from_boolean</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="PclObject">PclObject</link>*  pcl_bool_from_boolean           (<link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link> v_boolean);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns a new reference to either the built-in object <literal>True</literal> or <literal>False</literal>,
depending on the value of <parameter>v_boolean</parameter>.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>v_boolean</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a boolean value
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> a new reference to <literal>True</literal> or <literal>False</literal>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>

</refsect1>




